strategy: Create a unified filtered item CTE with color/price conditions. Use it to filter BOTH catalog tables in cs_ui AND store_sales early. Pre-join store_sales with filtered items and date_dim d1 (2001-2002
what_worked:
Applied prefetch_fact_join, single_pass_aggregation, early_filter: ** Created a unified `filtered_item` CTE with the item color/price conditions and used it to filter both catalog tables (in `cs_ui`) and store sales early. Pre-joined store sales with filtered items and date dimension d1 (for years 2001-2002) before joining with other dimensions. Restructured `cs_ui` to join catalog tables with filtered items first. This reduces the fact table joins by applying filters at the earliest possible stage.

**Expected speedup:** 2-3x by reducing the volume of catalog
why_it_worked: Pre-joining filtered dimensions with fact table before aggregation reduces join input; Consolidating repeated scans into CASE aggregates reduces I/O from N scans to 1; Applying selective filters early reduces intermediate row counts before expensive operations
